title: For Sale:  Overpriced Firearms
postcontent:
I've read a number of these angry postings on here where people are aggravated that Other people are trying to sell overpriced guns. This isn't always a bad thing. While I want to be quick to say I have neither listed or sold an overpriced gun on Armslist, I do believe these overpriced guns and ammo call attention to the need to stay armed and well stocked with ammo. If you were of age to buy an "assault" weapon during the Clinton administration and didn't ( but you meant to ), and just kept putting it off. These people need an incentive to buy an AR, AK or the weapon of their dreams.

If the "assault" rifles all dropped in price today, you would have a bunch of people that would decide to wait to get one. And the way it looks to me, every "assault" rifle sold gives me a better chance of keeping mine. If you don't HAVE ONE you might not be as concerned about others keeping theirs. We all need to be of one mind in this current gun grab attempt, and that is come hell or high water we are going to KEEP our rifles.

For some reason, when I see an AK priced at $1200.00, it just doesn't make me that mad. Why? Well because I won't buy it. I see overpriced cars on craigslist, I see overpriced steaks at the grocery, and lord help me if I have to buy medicine anywhere but Walmart. This is still America and the same constitution I believe in allows these fellows to ASK any price they want. 

And as far as reporting ANY gunowner for ANYTHING short of murder......well I just have to pause and give that a lot of consideration. I keep remembering the stories out of WWII of the German children that had been schooled by the government to report their families for infractions of the rules. Any person that is a gun owner is a friend of mine. I might not know your name or where you live, but I might need to borrow a few rounds one day or maybe loan you a few. So I guess if these boys want to sell a $3000.00 AR that walmart gets $600.00 for, I'm just going to read the ad, be proud I didn't have to spend that much on mine and let it blow past me. And if you NEED to be mad at someone, that fella that "stays" in the Whitehouse should be enough to work off All your mad.
